	err = damon_set_region_biggest_system_ram_default(param_target,
					&monitor_region_start,
					&monitor_region_end,
					param_ctx->min_region_sz);
...
	err = damon_commit_ctx(ctx, param_ctx);
```
Here's where it gets interesting. `damon_commit_ctx()` is used. My intuition is that it copies settings from `param_ctx` to the main `ctx` variable. This warrants a look at `damon_commit_ctx()` to confirm the parameter passing and data copying behavior.


