If we're tiering memory, we need to monitor the *entire* memory space, or at least both the fast and slow nodes. If DAMON only monitors a single node, it can't, for example, demote pages from the fast node to the slow node or promote pages from the slow node to the fast node. This is a complete contradiction to the whole goal of tiering memory!

